        "title": "fix: show WebChat preamble progress during tool activity",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Shows Codex/WebChat preamble and commentary progress in Control UI during tool activity.\n- Preserves pre-final stream commentary before final assistant messages.\n- Keeps keyed preamble segments independent from accumulated stream snapshots, supports keyed retraction, strips silent/directive-only progress, and preserves live timestamp ordering around tool cards.\n\n## Implementation\n- Projects Codex app-server `item` and `preamble` progress events into Control UI chat stream segments.\n- Splits keyed preambles from the existing tool-indexed accumulated stream lane.\n- Materializes pre-final segments by timestamp so history stays chronological.\n- Removes proof media from the branch; proof remains in PR evidence, not product tree.\n\n## Fleet-tool evidence\n- `pnpm lint --threads=8` (pass)\n- `pnpm exec vitest --run ui/src/ui/app-tool-stream.node.test.ts ui/src/ui/chat/build-chat-items.test.ts ui/src/ui/chat/stream-reconciliation.test.ts ui/src/ui/controllers/chat.test.ts` (201 passed)\n- `pnpm tsgo:test:ui` (pass)\n- `pnpm tsgo:core` (pass)\n- `git diff --check` (pass)\n- `CODEX_HOME=/home/lumadmin/.codex codex review --base origin/main` (pass, no discrete correctness issues found)\n- Crabbox fresh PR checkout: provider `local-container`, lease `cbx_d600f337df23`, Node `v24.17.0`, pnpm `11.2.2`, focused tests plus UI/core type lanes pass\n\n## CI / reviewer follow-up\n- CI rerun triggered by force-push to `533fba216826a7d29b34ab04b0f25277d0daf823`; latest poll: 1 passing, 5 pending, 2 skipped, 0 failing.\n- ClawSweeper re-review requested after the updated proof/code push.\n\n## AI disclosure\nThis PR was authored and submitted under ragesaq's GitHub identity. Implementation assistance was provided by Chisel via OpenAI Codex (`openai/gpt-5.5`). The evidence above lists the verification commands and review loop outputs used before requesting maintainer/bot review.",
